Returns an iterator that produces an escaped version of this slice,
treating it as an ASCII string.

# Examples

```
let s = b"0\t\r\n'\"\\\x9d";
let escaped = s.escape_ascii().to_string();
assert_eq!(escaped, "0\\t\\r\\n\\'\\\"\\\\\\x9d");
```
